Prof Chukwuma Charles Soludo, Anambra State Governor-elect has commiserated with Mr. Valentine Ozigbo, PDP gubernatorial candidate in the November 6, 2021, Anambra governorship election over the death of his father, Chief Andrew Nwafor Ozigbo who passed on January 3, 2022 In his condolence message to the Ozigbo’s family, made available to the media by Mr. Joe Anatune, the Governor-elect said he is deeply saddened by the passage of the Ozigbo Patriarch to the great beyond In his tribute to the departed Patriarch, Cee Cee Soludo described Chief Andrew Nwafor Ozigbo as a great community leader whose influence and contributions to his community impacted positively on the lives of the people of his community Happening Now: Old Aguata Union Honours Soludo With Royal Sword New Year Felicitation: Soludo Greets Ndi-Anambra, Hails Obiano He further described the deceased as a quintessential role model and an outstanding mentor not only to his children but to all who came across his path in his life time The Governor-elect stated further that his heart and prayers are with the Ozigbo’s at this trying moments while urging them to take solace in the comfort that comes from the Almighty Creator who has the final say in the lives of all mortals Soludo, therefore, prayed to God to grant the deceased eternal rest and the Ozigbo family the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss